    "body": "### Problem\r\nThe developer notes do not currently explain how test coverage should be placed across a commit stack.\r\nThis leaves room for [review friction](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/35251#discussion_r3217842286) around current-behavior tests, regression tests, and behavior-preserving refactors.\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\nAdd a short section describing the expected placement, clarifying that behavior-changing commits should carry the relevant coverage, that behavior-preserving refactors can omit tests when there is no externally observable behavior to test, and that characterization tests can be added first when they document uncovered current behavior before a later behavior change.",
